lay the fading Relics , which remain , In the still Vault ( excluding farther Pain ) ; Where Kings and Counsellors their Progress close , And his renowned Ancestors repose ; Where COVENTRY withdrew All but in Name , Leaving the World his Benefits and Fame ; Where his Paternal Predecessor lies , Once large of Thought , and ranked among the Wise ; Whose Genius in Long-Leat we may behold ( A Pile , as noble as if he'd been told By WEYMOUTH , it should be in time possessed , And strove to suit the Mansion to the Guest . )
